3 Lineup Detail
Confirmed lineups appear here when the match feed posts starting XIs.


Show code
if (nrow(board) &gt; 0) {
  lineup_detail &lt;- board |&gt;
    dplyr::filter(home_lineup_status == "Confirmed" | away_lineup_status == "Confirmed") |&gt;
    dplyr::select(
      date,
      match_label,
      home_formation,
      away_formation,
      home_starting_lineup,
      away_starting_lineup
    )

  if (nrow(lineup_detail) &gt; 0) {
    lineup_detail |&gt;
      display_table(caption = "Confirmed starting lineups.", max_rows = 8)
  } else {
    display_table(empty_note("Starting lineups update when the fixture feed posts them."))
  }
} else {
  display_table(empty_note("Lineup detail is available after the matchday board refresh."))
}





Note




Starting lineups update when the fixture feed posts them.

2 Model
The model predicts expected goals, usually written as lambda:
\[
\lambda = E(\text{Goals})
\]
Instead of fitting goals directly, the model fits the log of expected goals:
\[
\log(\lambda)
= \beta_0
+ \beta_1\text{Team Elo}
+ \beta_2\text{Opponent Elo}
+ \beta_3\text{Expected Result}
+ \beta_4\text{Listed Home}
+ \beta_5\text{Neutral Site}
\]
Plain English: the model estimates a positive expected-goals number from team strength, opponent strength, expected result, and match context.

