5 Model
The regression is:
\[
\text{Goals}
= \beta_0
+ \beta_1\text{Team Elo}
+ \beta_2\text{Opponent Elo}
+ \beta_3\text{Expected Result}
+ \beta_4\text{Listed Home}
+ \beta_5\text{Neutral Site}
+ \epsilon
\]
with:
\[
\epsilon_{i,m} \sim N(0, \sigma^2)
\]

4 Model
The model estimates the chance that a team result is at or below each ordered level:
\[
\text{logit}\left(P(\text{Result} \leq k)\right)
= \theta_k - \text{Team Score}
\]
where:
\[
k \in \{\text{loss}, \text{draw}\}
\]
and:
\[
\text{Team Score}
= \beta_1\text{Team Elo}
+ \beta_2\text{Opponent Elo}
+ \beta_3\text{Expected Result}
+ \beta_4\text{Listed Home}
+ \beta_5\text{Neutral Site}
\]

5 Probability View


Show code
if (nrow(predictions) &gt; 0 && requireNamespace("ggplot2", quietly = TRUE)) {
  wide_plot_data &lt;- predictions |&gt;
    dplyr::mutate(match = paste(home_team, "vs", away_team)) |&gt;
    dplyr::arrange(date, source_match_id) |&gt;
    dplyr::slice_head(n = 12) |&gt;
    dplyr::select(match, pred_home_win_prob, pred_draw_prob, pred_away_win_prob)

  plot_data &lt;- rbind(
    data.frame(match = wide_plot_data$match, outcome = "Home win", probability = wide_plot_data$pred_home_win_prob),
    data.frame(match = wide_plot_data$match, outcome = "Draw", probability = wide_plot_data$pred_draw_prob),
    data.frame(match = wide_plot_data$match, outcome = "Away win", probability = wide_plot_data$pred_away_win_prob)
  )
  plot_data$match &lt;- factor(plot_data$match, levels = rev(unique(wide_plot_data$match)))

  ggplot2::ggplot(plot_data, ggplot2::aes(x = probability, y = match, fill = outcome)) +
    ggplot2::geom_col(position = "stack", width = 0.72) +
    ggplot2::scale_x_continuous(labels = function(x) paste0(round(100 * x), "%")) +
    ggplot2::scale_fill_manual(values = c("Home win" = "#0f6b68", "Draw" = "#d9a441", "Away win" = "#b85c5c")) +
    ggplot2::labs(
      title = "Fixture result probabilities",
      x = "Predicted probability",
      y = NULL,
      fill = NULL
    ) +
    ggplot2::theme_minimal(base_size = 12)
} else {
  plot.new()
  text(0.5, 0.5, "Probability plot is available after the scoring refresh.")
}





Predicted home win, draw, and away win probabilities for upcoming fixtures.
